From [[Kanoe-no-Uma]] ({{ill|Kanoe-no-Uma|ja|庚午|1=Yang Metal Horse|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe-no-Uma|qq=}}, the seventh day from [[:en:Wood Rat|Yang Wood Rat]]) to [[Hinoe-no-Ne]] ({{ill|Hinoe-no-Ne|ja|1=Yang Fire Rat|2=ja|丙子|1=Yang Fire Rat|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoe-no-Ne|qq=}}, the thirteenth day), the seven days are called '''Dai-Hando''' (大犯土, "Great Hando" or "Great Earth"). From [[Tsuchinoe-no-Tora]] ({{ill|Tsuchinoe-no-Tora|ja|1=Yang Earth Tiger|2=ja|戊寅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoe-no-Tora|qq=}}, the fifteenth day) to [[Kanoe-no-Saru]] ({{ill|Kanoe-no-Saru|ja|1=Yang Wood Monkey|2=ja|甲申|1=Yang Wood Monkey|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe-no-Saru|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Wood Monkey|qq=}}, the twenty-first day), the seven days are called '''Sho-Hando''' (小犯土, "Small Hando" or "Small Earth"). The intervening day, [[Hinoe-no-Ushi]] ({{ill|Hinoe-no-Ushi|ja|1=Yin Fire Ox|2=ja|丁丑|1=Yin Fire Ox|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoe-no-Ushi|qq=}}, the fourteenth day), is referred to as '''Kanbi''' (間日, "Intercalary Day"), '''Hando Kanbi''' (犯土間日, "Intercalary Hando Day"), or '''Chu-Hando''' (中犯土, "Middle Hando"). This day is excluded from the Hando period or, alternatively, included but without the taboos associated with Hando.
